    <bioghist encodinganalog="545$a">
      <head>Historical Information
</head>
      <p>Richmond was established in 1742.  It was  incorporated as a town in 1782 and a city in 1842.  Richmond  annexed the city of Manchester in 1910; Barton Heights, Fairmont, and Highland Park in 1914; and part of Chesterfield County in 1970.
</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520$a">
      <head>Scope and Content
</head>
      <p>Richmond (Va.) Bill of Sale, November 1837.  Consists of a bill of sale documenting the sale of a negro boy named Dawson, two negro girls named Marinda and Dolley, and household and kitchen furniture from Francis H.S. Allen to William F. Stevenson for two thousand dollars.          
</p>
    </scopecontent>
